    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely dice your <strong>brown onion[s] </strong>then top, tail, peel and finely dice your <strong>carrot[s]</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> diced onion</strong> and <strong>carrot</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until softened and starting to caramelise</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lancashire-style-lamb-and-sweet-potato-hotpot/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, slice your <strong>sweet potato[es]</strong> (skin on) as thinly as you can</p><p>Add the <strong>sliced sweet potato</strong> to a pot of<strong> boiled water</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 2-3 min or until just cooked (this is known as 'parboiling')</p><p>Once done, drain the<strong> sliced sweet potato</strong> and leave them to steam dry</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lancashire-style-lamb-and-sweet-potato-hotpot/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the onion and carrot have softened, increase the heat to high, and add your <strong>lamb mince</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to brown, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p><p>Reboil half a kettle</p><p>Strip your<strong> thyme leaves</strong> from their stalks and chop them finely, discard the stalks</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lancashire-style-lamb-and-sweet-potato-hotpot/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the lamb has started to brown, stir in 1 tsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp] </span><strong>flour</strong> and cook for 30 secs</p><p>Stir in your <strong>tomato paste</strong>, <strong>Henderson's Relish</strong>,<strong> onion marmalade</strong>, <strong>bay leaf[ves]</strong> and <strong>half</strong> the<strong> chopped thyme </strong>(you'll use the rest later!)</p><p>Cook for 1 min and stir it all together to combine</p><p>Meanwhile, dissolve your <strong>beef stock mix </strong>in 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[225ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[300ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lancashire-style-lamb-and-sweet-potato-hotpot/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>beef stock</strong> to the pan and cook for 3-4 min or until thickened to a gravy-like consistency and the lamb is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>lamb mixture</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>lamb mixture</strong> to an <strong>oven-proof dish </strong>(reserve the pan for later)</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lancashire-style-lamb-and-sweet-potato-hotpot/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Layer the <strong>drained</strong> <strong>sliced sweet potato</strong> on top, dot them with a few knobs of <strong>butter</strong> and sprinkle with<strong> </strong>the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>chopped thyme</strong></p><p>Put the dish on a baking tray in the oven and cook for 25-30 min or until the potatoes are brown and crispy \u2013 this is your <strong>Lancashire-style lamb hotpot</strong></p><p>Once the Lancashire-style lamb hotpot is done, remove it from the oven and set aside to cool a little (this helps the flavours to develop and makes it easier to serve!)</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lancashire-style-lamb-and-sweet-potato-hotpot/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Wash your <strong>shredded kale</strong></p><p>Wipe the reserved pan clean and return to a medium heat with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>shredded kale </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and a small splash of <strong>water </strong>and cook for 2-3 min or until bright green and wilted \u2013 these are your <strong>wilted greens</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lancashire-style-lamb-and-sweet-potato-hotpot/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>Lancashire-style lamb & sweet potato hotpot</strong> with the <strong>wilted greens</strong> to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
